# T195 customer profile:
# TM195 is the most sold product(42%)   
# Median age of partnered female customers is 27, single females 26, partnered male 30 and single males 25
# More partnered females buy TM195 than partnered males and more single men buy TP195 than single women
# Majority of the customers rate their fitness 1-3
# low - medium usage folks prefer TM195 and TM498.
# customers Average education 

# T498 customer profile:
# TM195 is the mid range product, second most sold
# Median age of partnered female customers is 31, single females 25.5, partnered male 31 and single males 25.
# Majority of the customers rate their fitness 1-3
# both partnered and single women are equallly likely to buy T498 but more partnered men buy TM498 than single men
# Avg income of the customers is more than TM195 but less than TM498

# T798 customer profile:
# High end product. Less sold units.
# Customers buying TM798 are typically higher income and people above 70,000 are exclusively buying TM798
# Almost all people who rate their fitness 5 go for TM798
# TM798 has most customers with 16 and 18 years of education more than average(15.5)
# high usage folks tend to go for TM798  
# More males prefer this than females. Partnered males highest demographic
# 


# Recommendations for the company:

# T195 and TM498 can be targeted at mostly young professionals and students with low income.
# T195 is the budget model and TM498 a mid range product, so TM498 can be priced in at an attractive range close to TM195 so that we can drive more 
#     more customers are driven towards the mid range. 

# T798 is a premium end model- target high income , people who rate their fitness higher and who expect to use more
# T798 also seems more popular among males so. Run targeted add campaign for males with high income and fitness.
# T798 can be significantly priced higher (than T498) to generate more revenue as it is can be marketed as an exclusive
#    premium model for high income folks.
# T798 can be also be targeted at families with high income where usage can be high-> partnered high income males seem to 
#   like this model.
